data.content:
## .NET 10 OpenAPI Breaking Changes

The root cause is **Microsoft.OpenApi upgraded from v1 to v2**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1. Here are the breaking changes and fixes:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `IOpenApiAny` removed
The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead:

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `Nullable` property removed
OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's `type: ["string", "null"]` instead of a separate `nullable` flag. The `Nullable` property is gone; manipulate the `Type` flags enum instead:

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After — remove Null from the type flags
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

(Add `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;` — `JsonSchemaType` lives there.)

### 3. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` is no longer a dictionary
It no longer extends `Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>`. Use its `Schemes` property:

```csharp
// Before
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new()
    {
        Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
        {
            [oAuthScheme] = scopes
        }
    }
};
```

### 4. `ReferenceType` → string-based `ReferenceType`
The enum moved. Confirm the value still resolves — `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme` should still compile in v2, but if not, use the string overload on `OpenApiReference`.

---

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```
